history.content: 127 + 189 + 151 seems like death. I am currently taking 127 + 189 + TA'ing and it is very stressful/a lot of work.

children.subject: I am currently taking cs 170, ee 120 and cs 61c. Do you think this is comparable in terms of workload to 127, 189 and 151?

Not really. 170 + 120 might be comparable to 189 + 127 (in that order), but 151 is a step up from 61c in workload, mostly because all of the design in the labs/project is up to you. 

Whether you feel like you can make that step up is another question, and up to you.

Having taken 127 with 189 (in the fall), the classes do complement each other quite well. I never attended discussion for either and was able to do well, in large part because of the conceptual overlap. 

151 is quite a lot of work, but not particularly challenging conceptually. 

I would say that this schedule is doable if and only if you have the math background necessary to not struggle too much in 127 + 189 (e.g. taken 126 and did well). It'll probably be very painful regardless, though.

history.content: I am wondering if the EECS 127 workload and the CS 189 workload are a little lighter when you take the classes concurrently since you will be studying similar things. I was planning on taking these two combined with EECS 151, but am unsure as if EECS 127 will add an extreme amount of work to my schedule. Any advice?
